Use the standard library
This is how to median of l:
   Remember that a is bubble_sort of l
   Remember that n is a's length
   Remember that mid is quotient of n and 2
   Remember that parity is remainder of n and 2
   When parity is 1, then:
      The answer is item mid in a
   End when
   Remember that left is item (diff of mid and 1) in a
   Remember that right is item mid in a
   The answer is quotient of (sum of (tofloat of left) and (tofloat of right)) and (tofloat of 2)
Now you know
>>> median of [3, 1, 2, 4, 5] 
3
>>> median of [-10, 4, 6, 1000, 10, 20] 
8.000000
>>> median of [3, 1, 2, 4, 5] 
3